{
  "texts": [
    "For this reason, we study the b → sℓ -1 ℓ + 2 transition, both for ℓ 1 = ℓ 2 and ℓ 1 ̸ = ℓ 2, focusing on the exclusive modes B s → ℓ - 1 ℓ + 2, B → K * ℓ - 1 ℓ + 2 and B s → ϕℓ - 1 ℓ + 2for which a wealth of experimental information is available and some tensions are spotted.",
    "Moreover, we describe the leptonic LFV modes µ -→ e -γ, τ -→ µ -µ + µ -, µ -→ e -e + e -and the µ -→ e - conversion in nuclei.",
    "Finally, we consider the Z ′ contribution to (g -2) µ.",
    "Effective Hamiltonian forb → sℓ - 1 ℓ + 2The low-energy ∆B = -1, ∆S = 1 Hamiltonian governing b → sℓ - 1 ℓ + 2, comprising the SM operators for ℓ 1 = ℓ 2, and operators that can be generated in BSM models with Z ′, has the formH eff = -4 G F √ 2 V tb V * ts C 1 O 1 + C 2 O 2 + i=3,..,6 C i O i + i=7,..,10 [C i O i + C ′ i O ′ i].",
    "(38)G F is the Fermi constant, V ij are elements of the CKM matrix, and doubly Cabibbo suppressed terms proportional to V ub V * us are neglected."
  ]
}